title: Air Fryer Buffalo Chicken Wings from Frozen

Directions.1: Preheat an air fryer to 400 degrees F (200 degrees C).

Directions.2: Place wings in the air fryer basket.

Directions.3: Cook wings for 15 minutes, turn, and cook for 15 more minutes. Meanwhile, place wing sauce in a small saucepan and heat on low heat.

Directions.4: Flip wings one more time and cook until crispy, about 6 more minutes.

Directions.5: Transfer wings to a large bowl and pour warmed Buffalo wing sauce over the top. Toss and serve immediately.
